✅ SQL Data Types
     A data type defines the kind of data a column can store.
     It controls input, storage, and operations on data.

✅ Purpose
    -> Ensure correct data entry
    -> Improve performance
    -> Save memory/storage
    -> Maintain data consistency

✅ Types of Data Types
 1. Numeric Data Types
       Used to store numbers
Types:
      -> INT → whole numbers
      -> BIGINT → large integers
      -> DECIMAL(p,s) → exact decimal (money)
      -> FLOAT → approximate values

2. String (Character) Data Types
       Used to store text
Types:
      -> CHAR(n) → fixed length
      -> VARCHAR(n) → variable length
      -> TEXT → large text

3. Date & Time Data Types
       Used for date and time values
Types:
      -> DATE → date only
      -> TIME → time only
      -> DATETIME / TIMESTAMP → date + time

4. Boolean Data Type
      Stores TRUE or FALSE
Type:
      -> BOOLEAN

5. Binary Data Types
       Used to store files (images, videos)
Types:

-> BLOB
-> VARBINARY

✅ CHAR vs VARCHAR

| Feature | CHAR         | VARCHAR         |
| ------- | ------------ | --------------- |
| Length  | Fixed        | Variable        |
| Speed   | Faster       | Slightly slower |
| Storage | Wastes space | Saves space     |

✅ Data Type Comparison

1. Numeric Types

| Feature        | MySQL             | PostgreSQL                 | SQL Server      |
| -------------- | ----------------- | -------------------------- | --------------- |
| Integer        | INT, BIGINT       | INTEGER, BIGINT            | INT, BIGINT     |
| Auto Increment | AUTO_INCREMENT    | SERIAL / BIGSERIAL         | IDENTITY        |
| Exact Decimal  | DECIMAL(p,s)      | NUMERIC(p,s)               | DECIMAL(p,s)    |
| Float          | FLOAT, DOUBLE     | REAL, DOUBLE PRECISION     | FLOAT, REAL     |

 2. String Types

| Feature    | MySQL                      | PostgreSQL     | SQL Server                               |
| ---------- | -------------------------- | -------------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| Fixed      | CHAR(n)                    | CHAR(n)        | CHAR(n)                                  |
| Variable   | VARCHAR(n)                 | VARCHAR(n)     | VARCHAR(n)                               |
| Large Text | TEXT                       | TEXT           | TEXT (deprecated → use VARCHAR(MAX))     |
| Unicode    | VARCHAR (utf8 supported)   | Native Unicode | NVARCHAR                                 |

3. Date & Time Types

| Feature  | MySQL                   | PostgreSQL  | SQL Server              |
| -------- | ----------------------- | ----------- | ----------------------- |
| Date     | DATE                    | DATE        | DATE                    |
| Time     | TIME                    | TIME        | TIME                    |
| DateTime | DATETIME, TIMESTAMP     | TIMESTAMP   | DATETIME, DATETIME2     |

4. Boolean Type

| MySQL                        | PostgreSQL               | SQL Server  |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------------ | ----------- |
| BOOLEAN (alias of TINYINT)   | BOOLEAN (true boolean)   | BIT (0/1)   |

5. Special Types

| Feature | MySQL             | PostgreSQL               | SQL Server                  |
| ------- | ----------------- | ------------------------ | --------------------------- |
| JSON    | JSON              | JSON, JSONB (faster)     | JSON (stored in NVARCHAR)   |
| UUID    | UUID() function   | UUID type                | UNIQUEIDENTIFIER            |
| Array   | ❌Not supported   | ✅ Supported            | ❌ Not supported            |

